RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 25000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOXY ELAINE pressed the pace from the gate to the top of the lane and edged away in a determined drive down the lane. MORNING GORDITA stalked the pace from the fence through the turn, angled out three wide in upper stretch and surged for the place in the final stride. RUNTOLIVE set a pressured pace, kept on while dueling through the lane and was out-finished in deep stretch. ANGEL ON FIRE bumped at the start to drop to the rear of the field, cut the corner coming home and showed good late interest. C C GRAND tracked the leaders from two wide into the turn, faded back around the bend and finished evenly.

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, kept on, outfinished

ENTRY.OWNER: James Gary V and Lewis Robert E
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, trailed, late interest

ENTRY.NAME: Foxy Elaine
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, determined, edged clear

ENTRY.NAME: C C Grand
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked 2w, dropped back, never menaced

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRIGADIER GENERAL prompted the pace from two wide for the first half mile, assumed command into the turn, opened a clear advantage turning for home and finished well having never been threatened in the lane. PHANTOM RIDE stalked the pace from the fence saving ground into the far turn, angled out at the head of the lane and finished willingly a clear second best. ETHEREAL ROAD broke well out leaving the gate, raced up three wide to be well placed down the backstretch, ranged up into the final bend and finished evenly lacking a closing rally when called upon. C F V BULLET trailed for the first half, circled three wide with an early rally into the far turn and flattened out. PRINCE SHIM broke well to take the lead along the fence for the first half mile and steadily faded coming home.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 5 7 1/2F Turf CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 25000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. CLAIM.OWNER: Granitz Anthony J and Spooner Jake

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEEP STRIKE prompted the pace for the first half mile, rallied in the turn to take command at the head of the lane and drew off convincingly. PURPLE AURA tracked the leaders down the backside from three wide, made a bid midway on the turn under an early drive and finished well down the lane maintaining his rally. MIDNIGHT TIL DAWN stalked the pace to the head of the lane while having worked to the rail saving ground and finished willingly up the fence. YELLOW JACKET well placed in mid-pack down the backside, was bumped by PLAY THE TRUMPET and hemmed in entering the far turn while looking for racing room, waited from between horses to the upper stretch and rallied down the lane through traffic in a rough trip. BACHMAN unhurried early on to be near the rear for the first half mile and made a mild bid in the stretch to be gaining ground. PLAY THE TRUMPET in tight early down the lane the first time while racing up the rail, worked his way out down the backside, exchanged bumps in the far turn, rallied five wide and finished evenly. TORMENTA JERRY set a pressured pace for the three quarters of a mile and weakened in the stretch. HADLEY'S MAX attempted to get out on the first turn racing wide, settled through the turn and went one-paced failing to menace. FIREBALL JUSTICE was never a threat. BUDGET BOOSTER was outrun.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CODE OMAHA broke sharp to open a clear advantage shortly away from the gate, was challenged in mid-stretch, responded and drew away to the wire in a convincing manner. SILENT HEART squeezed back at the start to trail, steadily gained ground through the turn and closed well belatedly for the place. AZTECA'S GOLD tracked the leaders down the backside, rallied in the turn to loom boldly in upper stretch and was out-kicked down the lane. WEEKEND CONCERTO prompted the pace from five wide in the turn to be prominent at the head of the lane and failed to sustain his rally. ELM STREET tracked the pace from the rail in a five horse pack in the turn, checked sharply when a rival impeded several on the turn, lost position and came on again well down the lane. HABERDASHERY stalked the pace in the turn from between rivals three wide, dropped to the inside causing the inside two rivals to take up on the turn, was well placed turning for home and flattened out in the drive. DADDY'S DINERO raced between rivals prominently into the turn, was forced to take up when impeded by HABERDASHERY on the bend and bumped the inside rival crowding him against the rail, was taken in hand, settled and finished evenly. GOOD POINT raced four wide in the turn to be well placed, was checked late in the turn and dropped back failing to re-rally. IZZIT MIDNIGHT was never a threat.
